vibera
======

Voice-controlled AI staff officer for OpenRA Red Alert 1.

Copyright (c) 2026 Mark Boo
Licensed under the MIT License (see LICENSE).

This project is an *external* control client for OpenRA. It does not bundle
or redistribute OpenRA source or assets. To run vibera you must install
OpenRA separately and apply the patch in `patches/openra-port.patch`, which
exposes the ExternalControl trait on a non-default port (7778).

Third-party software
--------------------

OpenRA (https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA)
    Licensed under GPLv3. vibera communicates with OpenRA over a TCP
    socket; this is "mere aggregation" and does not affect vibera's MIT
    license. The patch in `patches/` is a derivative work of OpenRA and is
    therefore distributed under GPLv3 (see header in the patch file).

pywhispercpp (https://github.com/abdeladim-s/pywhispercpp)
    MIT-licensed Python bindings for whisper.cpp.

whisper.cpp (https://github.com/ggerganov/whisper.cpp)
    MIT-licensed C/C++ port of OpenAI Whisper.

google-genai (https://github.com/googleapis/python-genai)
    Apache-2.0.

PyObjC (https://github.com/ronaldoussoren/pyobjc)
    MIT-licensed.

